UI Policies (ServiceNow)
🔹 What are UI Policies?

UI Policies in ServiceNow are used to dynamically control form behavior without writing scripts. They help manage how fields appear and behave based on conditions.

🔹 Features
Show or hide fields
Make fields mandatory
Set fields as read-only
Execute changes dynamically
Works without client-side scripting
🔹 UI Policy Actions

UI Policy Actions define what happens to fields when conditions are met.

Common Actions
Visible → Show or hide field
Mandatory → Make field required
Read Only → Prevent editing
🔹 Components
1. UI Policy

Defines the condition and when it should run.

2. UI Policy Action

Defines which fields are affected and what action is applied.

🔹 Example

Scenario:
If State = Closed

Then:

Close Notes → Editable
All other fields → Read Only

Condition:

State = Closed

Actions:

Short Description → Read Only = True
Priority → Read Only = True
Close Notes → Read Only = False
🔹 Benefits
Reduces scripting effort
Improves user experience
Ensures data consistency
Easy to configure and maintain
🔹 Types
Form UI Policy
Catalog UI Policy
